    <string name="keys1">Different types of area calculation can allow landowners, amins, server to measure any land shape accurately using standard international metrics or traditional Bangladeshi units.</string>
    <string name="keys02">An integrated Local Unit Calculation provides invaluable localized utility, ensuring everyone can compute using the exact, historical regional systems native to their home districts. </string>
    <string name="keys2">It has Steel Rod Calculation, Gold Calculation, Timber Calculation, Soil Calculation for helping users.</string>
    <string name="keys3">A built-in GPS Tracker that records and stores GPX files locally offline adds massive value for field engineers, loggers, and surveyors who work in remote areas with zero cellular coverage.</string>
    <string name="keys4">A built-in GeoTag Image feature provides users with definitive visual proof of their survey locations by embedding precise location metadata directly into the image file.</string>
    <string name="keys5">A built-in Digital Compass provides users with immediate, offline orientation, which is help measuring land boundaries.</string>
    <string name="keys6">A built-in Audio Recorder allows surveyors and field engineers to capture hands-free verbal notes, keeping their eyes on the project while preserving critical site details for future use.</string>
    <string name="keys7">Integrating a Basic Calculator into the tool eliminates app-switching, allowing users to perform quick arithmetic directly alongside their specialized material and survey modules.</string>
    <string name="keys8">An integrated Notebook allows field workers to write down critical observations, measurements, and project details in one secure place alongside their calculations and GPS data.</string>
    <string name="keys9">An integrated Unit Converter completes your utility toolkit by allowing users to instantly translate measurements between different regional and international standards without leaving the app. </string>
    <string name="keys10">A built-in Data Collection Form acts as the central data aggregator for your application, allowing field surveyors to compile all work info, calculations, and media into a professional project report that can be shared instantly with clients.</string>
    <string name="keys11">Stopwatch, Counter, and Drawing Tools completes your applications field toolkit, giving Amins and server the exact utility features needed for timing equipment, counting assets, and sketching plots onsite.</string>





